WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.600 --> 00:00:04.970 align:start size:34% position:66% line:0%
♪♪

00:00:04.970 --> 00:00:07.907
Narrator:
CLAY TARGETS ARE MADE
TO BE DESTROYED

00:00:07.907 --> 00:00:11.077
THE VERY FIRST TIME
THEY'RE USED.

00:00:11.077 --> 00:00:13.713
MANUFACTURED IN MULTIPLE COLORS,

00:00:13.713 --> 00:00:17.584
THESE INVERTED SAUCERS
ARE USED AS PRACTICE TARGETS

00:00:17.584 --> 00:00:22.522
AND CAN BE LAUNCHED BY HAND
OR THROUGH AUTOMATED MACHINES.

00:00:24.056 --> 00:00:27.293
[ HIP HOP PLAYS ]
ALSO REFERRED TO
AS CLAY PIGEONS,

00:00:27.293 --> 00:00:30.396
THESE TARGETS ARE NOT
ACTUALLY MADE OF CLAY.

00:00:30.396 --> 00:00:31.931
THEY'RE MADE WITH PITCH,

00:00:31.931 --> 00:00:35.001
A CERAMIC-TYPE MATERIAL,
OR RESIN.

00:00:35.001 --> 00:00:36.702
SINCE THE 1920s,

00:00:36.702 --> 00:00:39.839 line:0%
THIS FRENCH COMPANY
HAS BEEN PRODUCING CLAY SAUCERS

00:00:39.839 --> 00:00:42.742 line:0%
FOR BOTH TARGET PRACTICE
AND COMPETITIONS,

00:00:42.742 --> 00:00:44.710
INCLUDING THE OLYMPICS.

00:00:44.710 --> 00:00:46.045
THE FOUNDER INVENTED

00:00:46.045 --> 00:00:50.850
THE FIRST AUTOMATED TARGET-
MOLDING MACHINE IN 1947.

00:00:50.850 --> 00:00:53.686
PITCH TARGETS ARE MADE
FROM PETROLEUM PITCH,

00:00:53.686 --> 00:00:56.222
A SUBSTANCE DERIVED
FROM CRUDE OIL;

00:00:56.222 --> 00:01:00.259
AND CALCIUM CARBONATE,
COMMONLY KNOWN AS TALC.

00:01:00.259 --> 00:01:02.094
TALC IS THE FILLER,

00:01:02.094 --> 00:01:05.064
WHILE PETROLEUM PITCH
IS THE BINDING AGENT,

00:01:05.064 --> 00:01:08.767
WHICH SOLIDIFIES INTO A HARD,
BRITTLE MATERIAL.

00:01:08.767 --> 00:01:14.273
THE TALC ARRIVES TO THE FACTORY
HEATED AT 176° FAHRENHEIT.

00:01:14.273 --> 00:01:16.209
A TECHNICIAN
TRANSFERS THE TALC

00:01:16.209 --> 00:01:20.379
FROM THE TRUCK
TO A HEATED STORAGE SILO.

00:01:20.379 --> 00:01:23.082
A SCREW CONVEYOR MOVES
THE TALC FROM THE SILO

00:01:23.082 --> 00:01:26.185
TO THE BLENDER TANK,
MIXING IT WITH THE PITCH.

00:01:26.185 --> 00:01:29.722 align:start size:34% position:66% line:0%
♪♪

00:01:29.722 --> 00:01:32.258
THE PETROLEUM PITCH ARRIVES
TO THE FACTORY

00:01:32.258 --> 00:01:34.994 line:0%
HEATED TO 392°.

00:01:34.994 --> 00:01:38.264 line:0%
THE PITCH IS TRANSFERRED
TO A HEATED STORAGE SILO

00:01:38.264 --> 00:01:39.799 line:0%
AND PUMPED INTO A BLENDER.

00:01:39.799 --> 00:01:41.901 align:start size:34% position:66% line:0%
♪♪

00:01:41.901 --> 00:01:45.804
EVERY 10 SECONDS,
22 POUNDS OF PETROLEUM PITCH

00:01:45.804 --> 00:01:49.575
AND 64 POUNDS OF TALC
ARE RELEASED INTO THE BLENDER.

00:01:49.575 --> 00:01:51.911 align:start size:34% position:66% line:0%
♪♪

00:01:51.911 --> 00:01:56.181
THE MATERIALS COOL AS SOON
AS THEY LEAVE THE HEATED SILOS.

00:01:56.181 --> 00:02:02.287
A GAS BOILER REHEATS
THE INGREDIENTS IN 509° OIL.

00:02:02.287 --> 00:02:05.458
THE HOT OIL CIRCULATES IN PIPES
AROUND THE BLENDER,

00:02:05.458 --> 00:02:09.562
HEATING THE PITCH-TALC
MIXTURE TO ABOUT 390°.

00:02:09.562 --> 00:02:13.499
THIS PROCESS CHANGES
THE CONSISTENCY TO A PASTE.

00:02:13.499 --> 00:02:15.534
THE PASTE
FLOWS FROM THE BLENDER

00:02:15.534 --> 00:02:18.037
TO THE AUTOMATIC
MOLDING MACHINE.

00:02:18.037 --> 00:02:21.039
THIS VALVE CUTS THE FLOW
AT REGULAR INTERVALS

00:02:21.039 --> 00:02:24.310
TO TIME THE INJECTIONS
INTO THE TARGET-SHAPED MOLDS.

00:02:24.310 --> 00:02:25.911 align:start size:34% position:66% line:0%
♪♪

00:02:25.911 --> 00:02:29.581
THE MACHINE COMPRESSES THE PASTE
WHILE COOLING IT WITH WATER,

00:02:29.581 --> 00:02:31.317
SO THAT IT SOLIDIFIES.

00:02:31.317 --> 00:02:33.953 align:start size:34% position:66% line:0%
♪♪

00:02:33.953 --> 00:02:36.222
A TRANSFER DEVICE
MOVES THE TARGETS

00:02:36.222 --> 00:02:38.991
ONTO A CONVEYER BELT
ONE AT A TIME.

00:02:38.991 --> 00:02:41.294
AS THEY MOVE TO THE
NEXT CONVEYER BELT,

00:02:41.294 --> 00:02:43.296
THE MOLDS ARE FLIPPED
RIGHT-SIDE-UP.

00:02:43.296 --> 00:02:45.331 align:start size:34% position:66% line:0%
♪♪

00:02:45.331 --> 00:02:47.566
EVEN THOUGH THE MOLDS
ARE STILL HOT,

00:02:47.566 --> 00:02:49.702
THEY'VE REMAINED SOFT
AND PLIABLE.

00:02:49.702 --> 00:02:52.571 align:start size:34% position:66% line:0%
♪♪

00:02:52.571 --> 00:02:55.508
AS THE TARGETS CONTINUE
TO COOL AND HARDEN,

00:02:55.508 --> 00:02:57.409
A SEPARATING DEVICE
LINES THEM UP

00:02:57.409 --> 00:03:00.546 line:0%
FOR THE CONVEYER BELTS
THAT GO TO THE PAINT CHAMBERS.

00:03:00.546 --> 00:03:04.583 align:start size:34% position:66% line:0%
♪♪

00:03:04.583 --> 00:03:07.553
THE PAINT IS MADE PRIMARILY
OF CARBONATE

00:03:07.553 --> 00:03:09.822
AND BIODEGRADABLE
POWDERED PIGMENT.

00:03:09.822 --> 00:03:12.191 align:start size:34% position:66% line:0%
♪♪

00:03:12.191 --> 00:03:15.194 line:0%
A TECHNICIAN POURS
A PREMEASURED AMOUNT OF WATER...

00:03:15.194 --> 00:03:18.197 align:start size:34% position:66% line:0%
♪♪

00:03:18.197 --> 00:03:20.433 line:0%
...AND A BAG OF PIGMENT
INTO A MIXER.

00:03:20.433 --> 00:03:23.535 align:start size:34% position:66% line:0%
♪♪

00:03:23.535 --> 00:03:26.238 line:0%
THE MIXER COMBINES
THE INGREDIENTS TOGETHER.

00:03:26.238 --> 00:03:30.176 align:start size:34% position:66% line:0%
♪♪

00:03:30.176 --> 00:03:32.878
ONCE THE WATER AND PIGMENT
HAVE BLENDED TOGETHER,

00:03:32.878 --> 00:03:34.646
A PRE-MEASURED AMOUNT
OF CARBONATE

00:03:34.646 --> 00:03:36.049
IS ADDED TO THE MIXER,

00:03:36.049 --> 00:03:38.984
ALONG WITH A BINDING
AND THICKENING AGENT.

00:03:38.984 --> 00:03:41.721
AFTER ADDITIONAL BLENDING,
THE PAINT IS READY.

00:03:41.721 --> 00:03:43.455 align:start size:34% position:66% line:0%
♪♪

00:03:43.455 --> 00:03:45.324
THE TARGETS MOVE
FROM THE CONVEYER BELT

00:03:45.324 --> 00:03:46.892
ONTO SPINNING HOLDERS,

00:03:46.892 --> 00:03:49.395
WHICH CARRY THE TARGETS
THROUGH THE PAINT CHAMBER.

00:03:49.395 --> 00:03:53.265 align:start size:34% position:66% line:0%
♪♪

00:03:53.265 --> 00:03:57.069
INSIDE, A SPRAYER COATS THE
SPINNING TARGETS WITH PAINT.

00:03:57.069 --> 00:03:59.972 align:start size:34% position:66% line:0%
♪♪

00:03:59.972 --> 00:04:03.342 line:0%
THE TARGETS EXIT THE CHAMBER
WET AND COOLED.

00:04:03.342 --> 00:04:07.513 align:start size:34% position:66% line:0%
♪♪

00:04:07.513 --> 00:04:09.548
ANOTHER SEPARATOR
DIVIDES THE TARGETS

00:04:09.548 --> 00:04:11.851
ONTO TWO CONVEYER BELTS,

00:04:11.851 --> 00:04:14.052
WHICH CARRY THEM
THROUGH A HOT-AIR TUNNEL

00:04:14.052 --> 00:04:16.288
FOR 30 SECONDS,
TO DRY THE PAINT.

00:04:16.288 --> 00:04:20.526 align:start size:34% position:66% line:0%
♪♪

00:04:20.526 --> 00:04:23.629
THE CONVEYER BELT FEEDS
THE TARGETS TO A MACHINE,

00:04:23.629 --> 00:04:25.865
WHICH PILES THEM IN STACKS.

00:04:25.865 --> 00:04:28.835 align:start size:34% position:66% line:0%
♪♪

00:04:28.835 --> 00:04:33.872
CLAY PIGEONS CAN BE MANUFACTURED
IN SEVERAL SIZES.

00:04:33.872 --> 00:04:36.808
OLYMPIC REGULATION SIZE
IS THE LARGEST,

00:04:36.808 --> 00:04:38.978
CONTAINING A WIDTH
OF 4 INCHES.

00:04:38.978 --> 00:04:42.215 align:start size:34% position:66% line:0%
♪♪

00:04:42.215 --> 00:04:45.818
A SMALLER TARGET IS USED
FOR TRAINING PURPOSES

00:04:45.818 --> 00:04:48.587
AND CONTAINS A WIDTH
UNDER 4 INCHES.

00:04:48.587 --> 00:04:50.389 align:start size:34% position:66% line:0%
♪♪

00:04:50.389 --> 00:04:52.424
REGARDLESS OF THEIR SIZE,

00:04:52.424 --> 00:04:55.995
ALL TARGETS ARE ENGINEERED
TO REMAIN STABLE IN FLIGHT

00:04:55.995 --> 00:04:59.599
WHILE FOLLOWING THE INTENDED
TRAJECTORY AND, FINALLY,

00:04:59.599 --> 00:05:01.233
SHATTER WHEN SHOT.

00:05:01.233 --> 00:05:03.036 align:start size:34% position:66% line:0%
♪♪

